1
00:00:47,361 --> 00:00:49,454
[ Man ]
Don't tell me
about my visa.

2
00:00:49,496 --> 00:00:53,398
My wife is stuck in that hellhole, 
and I am getting on that plane.

3
00:00:59,306 --> 00:01:02,867
It's bad,Joe.
They're evacuating the villages.

4
00:01:02,943 --> 00:01:06,811
The roads are washed out.
We're hearing gunfire now.

5
00:01:06,880 --> 00:01:10,543
Can you--
Can you get to Calamar?

6
00:01:10,617 --> 00:01:14,553
Can you get across the border
to Colombia?

7
00:01:14,621 --> 00:01:18,216
They're putting us on the bus.
I don't know where they're taking us.

8
00:01:20,427 --> 00:01:23,919
Joe? Joe?

9
00:01:23,997 --> 00:01:26,431
Emily! Em--

10
00:01:41,047 --> 00:01:44,483
[ Baby Crying ]

11
00:01:54,995 --> 00:01:58,089
[ All Screaming ]

12
00:02:11,144 --> 00:02:12,941
[ Screaming Continues ]

13
00:02:18,452 --> 00:02:22,047
Emily Darrow was not
just a doctor...

14
00:02:22,122 --> 00:02:24,750
and a credit
to the medical profession...

15
00:02:24,825 --> 00:02:29,626
she was a healer
and a credit to the human race.

16
00:02:29,696 --> 00:02:32,722
Those who knew her
were changed by her...

17
00:02:32,799 --> 00:02:35,290
inspired by her commitment
to give...

18
00:02:35,368 --> 00:02:37,962
literally everything
of herself...

19
00:02:38,038 --> 00:02:40,836
which is why
we're gathered here today--

20
00:02:40,907 --> 00:02:44,502
to celebrate
this unique life...

21
00:02:44,578 --> 00:02:47,741
not so much taken from us...

22
00:02:47,814 --> 00:02:49,748
as given to us.

23
00:02:49,816 --> 00:02:53,013
From her colleagues
at the university...

24
00:02:53,086 --> 00:02:55,680
to her young patients here...

25
00:02:55,755 --> 00:02:59,384
in Chicago Memorial's
pediatric oncology ward...

26
00:02:59,459 --> 00:03:02,758
she will be sorely missed.

27
00:03:05,031 --> 00:03:08,194
We're told in medical school that
the face of an emergency room doctor...

28
00:03:08,268 --> 00:03:11,601
is the last thing a lot
of people will ever see.

29
00:03:11,671 --> 00:03:15,732
I've tried to keep that in mind when I
see those frightened eyes staring out at me.

30
00:03:15,809 --> 00:03:18,744
But I don't know
what Emily saw.

31
00:03:19,846 --> 00:03:21,780
What image she took with her.

32
00:03:21,848 --> 00:03:24,578
If there was
a compassionate face...

33
00:03:24,651 --> 00:03:27,848
or she died
in a world of chaos.

34
00:03:27,921 --> 00:03:30,389
And that I don't know this...

35
00:03:30,457 --> 00:03:32,618
haunts me.

36
00:03:32,692 --> 00:03:36,458
The divers saw inside, señor.
There is no one alive.

37
00:03:36,530 --> 00:03:39,624
Then where is she?
Where's her body?

38
00:03:39,699 --> 00:03:41,690
We are searching the shoreline
and jungle now...

39
00:03:41,735 --> 00:03:44,169
but the bus is
under ten feet of water.

40
00:03:44,237 --> 00:03:46,637
The river runs at 17 miles
an hour, señor.

41
00:03:46,706 --> 00:03:48,640
There is nothing
you can do.

42
00:03:48,708 --> 00:03:50,699
Por favor, go home.

43
00:03:52,479 --> 00:03:55,277
I'm not going anywhere.

44
00:03:55,348 --> 00:03:57,839
Not till this is over.

45
00:03:57,918 --> 00:04:01,410
I assure you, señor,
it's over.

46
00:04:11,331 --> 00:04:14,232
- [ Siren Wailing ]
- [ Horn Honking ]

47
00:04:27,614 --> 00:04:30,549
No vitals, no pulse.
Put him in E.R. Three on the left.

48
00:04:30,617 --> 00:04:32,209
What are you doing here?
I was paged.

49
00:04:32,285 --> 00:04:34,651
What do we have? Wasn't this morning
your wife's memorial service?

50
00:04:34,721 --> 00:04:37,519
There's nothing I can do for her, okay?
Except keep anyone from joining her.

51
00:04:37,591 --> 00:04:39,525
Now, what do we have?
Six-car pileup.

52
00:04:39,593 --> 00:04:42,926
Eleven injuries. Four went over to County
and six are coming here.

53
00:04:42,996 --> 00:04:45,931
All right, let's go.
Stay with me. How extensive?

54
00:04:45,999 --> 00:04:48,490
Third degree. Forty percent, maybe 50.
Did you tube him?

55
00:04:48,568 --> 00:04:51,264
- Airway's crushed. Couldn't do a cryc.
- Pronounce him.

56
00:04:51,338 --> 00:04:54,307
- Hit the windshield.
- All right, that's a blowout fracture.

57
00:04:54,374 --> 00:04:56,535
Get a C.T. Find out
what else he's got.

58
00:04:56,610 --> 00:05:00,341
What's this?
O.D. Attempted suicide.

59
00:05:00,413 --> 00:05:03,871
Give her to Simon. I'm interested in
people who want to live tonight.

60
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:06,350
- What's her term?
- She hit the steering wheel.

61
00:05:06,419 --> 00:05:10,185
- How pregnant? Anybody know?
- She looks no more than six months to me.

62
00:05:10,256 --> 00:05:13,521
- She's souring. Let's get it out.
- At six months?

63
00:05:13,593 --> 00:05:16,460
It might have a chance,
but not in there.
Look at her color.

64
00:05:16,529 --> 00:05:19,498
It's still got a heartbeat.
Let's get it out of there.

65
00:05:19,566 --> 00:05:23,400
-This requires consultation--
-Yeah, and let's order out for
pizza while we're at it. Move.

66
00:05:23,470 --> 00:05:26,371
There's a procedure
in place for terminating
a pregnancy, Joe.

67
00:05:26,439 --> 00:05:29,169
I'm not terminating
a pregnancy.
I'm delivering a baby.

68
00:05:29,242 --> 00:05:31,437
Get Prenatal
down here now.

69
00:05:40,654 --> 00:05:42,588
It was the right call.

70
00:05:42,656 --> 00:05:45,557
Delivering a technically
unviable fetus
by Caesarean section...

71
00:05:45,625 --> 00:05:48,025
without consultation
or permission of the mother--

72
00:05:48,094 --> 00:05:50,790
Who was dead.
Not officially.

73
00:05:50,864 --> 00:05:53,389
The baby's alive, Hugh.

74
00:05:55,135 --> 00:05:58,502
I'm concerned, Joe.
So is the rest of the staff.

75
00:05:58,571 --> 00:06:02,337
You refused to treat
a suicide today.
I passed her on to Simon.

76
00:06:02,409 --> 00:06:05,139
As though she were
unworthy of you.

77
00:06:07,113 --> 00:06:09,206
Can we discuss this
tomorrow?

78
00:06:09,282 --> 00:06:13,480
Since Emily's death,
you have been working
around the clock...

79
00:06:13,553 --> 00:06:16,249
24-hour shifts, I'm told,
seven days a week.

80
00:06:16,322 --> 00:06:19,780
Think I'm losing my edge?
Just the opposite.
It's getting too sharp.

81
00:06:19,859 --> 00:06:24,853
You're starting to cut
people around here.
You need time off.

82
00:06:24,931 --> 00:06:26,865
You need to grieve.

83
00:06:28,668 --> 00:06:30,898
I need to grieve?
Mm-hmm.

84
00:06:38,478 --> 00:06:40,708
I am serious, Joe.

85
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:43,214
Take that time off.

86
00:06:57,263 --> 00:06:59,493
Was it you
who reported me?

87
00:07:01,167 --> 00:07:03,192
Passing on the suicide?

88
00:07:08,808 --> 00:07:11,242
How is she doing?

89
00:07:11,311 --> 00:07:14,075
She's waiting for a bed
on the psych ward.

90
00:07:49,482 --> 00:07:53,350
- Why did you do this to me?
- Do what to you?

91
00:07:55,522 --> 00:07:57,513
Bring me back.

92
00:07:57,590 --> 00:07:59,956
Where were you going?

93
00:08:01,027 --> 00:08:02,892
Someplace better.

94
00:08:02,962 --> 00:08:06,295
Is that right?
I'll do it again too.

95
00:08:06,366 --> 00:08:08,698
It's all I want now.

96
00:08:10,770 --> 00:08:13,295
Well, unfortunately,
your heart disagrees.

97
00:08:14,407 --> 00:08:16,637
It's waged quite
a battle tonight.

98
00:08:19,679 --> 00:08:22,341
No one knows my heart.

99
00:08:22,415 --> 00:08:24,440
[ Sobbing ]

100
00:08:25,718 --> 00:08:27,982
Maybe that's why
it's still beating--

101
00:08:30,089 --> 00:08:32,182
to give somebody
a chance to.

102
00:08:37,230 --> 00:08:41,326
Let me tell you
about that better place
you think you're going to.

103
00:08:42,602 --> 00:08:45,765
You better be
damn sure it's there.

104
00:08:45,839 --> 00:08:49,275
'Cause crappy
as this place is,
it's all there is.

105
00:08:51,044 --> 00:08:55,413
So go ahead.
Be my guest.

106
00:08:55,481 --> 00:08:58,939
But when you
never wake up again,
don't say I didn't warn you.

107
00:09:04,924 --> 00:09:08,451
Hi, Father.
Time for a rebuttal?

108
00:09:08,528 --> 00:09:12,760
[ Thunder Rumbles ]

109
00:09:12,832 --> 00:09:17,735
'And on her footfall,
in rustle of leaves...

110
00:09:17,804 --> 00:09:20,068
"her whisper on the wind...

111
00:09:20,139 --> 00:09:23,404
she speaks from a place
beyond mortal pain."

112
00:09:23,476 --> 00:09:25,603
Hey, look who's here.
Joe!

113
00:09:25,678 --> 00:09:28,909
Hey, you!
You're just in time
to finish the toast.

114
00:09:28,982 --> 00:09:32,145
Pour him a beer.
Linda, can I have
another one, please?

115
00:09:32,218 --> 00:09:35,984
Hey, Joe, "Rachel in Heaven"
Remember that poem,
third-year lit class?

116
00:09:36,055 --> 00:09:39,218
Remember?
Yeah.
To Emily.

117
00:09:39,292 --> 00:09:41,886
To Emily.

118
00:09:44,297 --> 00:09:46,424
How are things
in the hospital?

119
00:09:46,499 --> 00:09:49,263
I don't know why we try
so hard to save them...

120
00:09:49,335 --> 00:09:51,769
if they've got
such a wonderful place
to go...

121
00:09:51,838 --> 00:09:54,602
Iike "Rachel in Heaven."

122
00:09:54,674 --> 00:09:57,074
That's where Emily is.
You can bet on that.

123
00:09:57,143 --> 00:09:58,474
If anyone deserved
to go there, it was her.

124
00:09:58,511 --> 00:10:01,571
Hear, hear.
She was the best of us.
The best of us.

125
00:10:01,648 --> 00:10:03,775
I don't know
what the hell
she saw in you, though.

126
00:10:03,850 --> 00:10:06,819
Lord knows I tried
for years to talk her
out of it.

127
00:10:08,354 --> 00:10:12,791
She was the best of us.
And I have no idea
what she saw in me.

128
00:10:12,859 --> 00:10:16,192
She saw the second
best of us.
You were a great team.

129
00:10:16,262 --> 00:10:20,028
She was the heart,
you were the mind.
Together, you were unbeatable.

130
00:10:30,877 --> 00:10:33,107
Where are you, Joe?

131
00:10:34,847 --> 00:10:39,181
Nowhere.
I'm gonna go.

132
00:10:39,252 --> 00:10:41,550
No, come on, man.
You just got here.

133
00:10:41,621 --> 00:10:44,181
Like you said, Eric,
I'm a mind
without a heart.

134
00:10:44,257 --> 00:10:46,487
Joe, come on.
Joe, that's not--

135
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:49,585
Don't leave, Joe.

136
00:10:49,662 --> 00:10:53,189
Buddy, that is not
what I meant.
I know
you didn't mean it.

137
00:10:54,434 --> 00:10:57,892
But you were right on, buddy.
I love you anyway.

138
00:10:57,971 --> 00:11:00,201
All of you.

139
00:11:00,273 --> 00:11:02,138
Thank you
for coming today.

140
00:11:03,609 --> 00:11:05,543
See ya.

141
00:11:23,730 --> 00:11:28,030
Hey, Doc.
[ Coughs ]
Hey, Miriam.

142
00:11:28,101 --> 00:11:32,401
Sorry I missed the service.
I didn't want to cough
all over everybody.

143
00:11:32,472 --> 00:11:34,463
Was it nice?

144
00:11:34,540 --> 00:11:36,940
I guess.

145
00:11:37,010 --> 00:11:38,944
I couldn't handle it.

146
00:11:39,012 --> 00:11:43,073
Well, then you're not
gonna do too good with this.

147
00:11:43,149 --> 00:11:47,051
They needed somebody to sign
for it. I didn't want to
leave it out in the rain.

148
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:50,817
It's a toy company
in Texas.

149
00:11:50,890 --> 00:11:53,051
That'll teach her
to shop the lnternet.

150
00:11:53,126 --> 00:11:56,926
Yeah, that'll teach her.

151
00:11:56,996 --> 00:12:00,056
You'd think a professor
of law could be more precise
with her language.

152
00:12:00,133 --> 00:12:03,227
It's all right.
You have a good night.

153
00:12:05,772 --> 00:12:09,037
Hey, I saw through the
kitchen window Big Bird
didn't eat again.

154
00:12:09,108 --> 00:12:13,545
- Should he go back to the vet?
- The vet said Big Bird
will outlive us all.

155
00:12:13,613 --> 00:12:16,411
[ Laughs ]

156
00:12:21,220 --> 00:12:23,484
[ Crackling ]

157
00:12:23,556 --> 00:12:25,751
[ Phone Ringing ]

158
00:12:31,097 --> 00:12:33,224
[ Answering Machine Beeps ]
Hey,Joe, it's Hal.

159
00:12:33,299 --> 00:12:35,961
I forgot to tell you
we are going on that
white-water trip.

160
00:12:36,035 --> 00:12:38,435
[ Eric ] Gotta come,Joe!
[ Flora ] Don't leave me
alone with these guys!

161
00:12:38,504 --> 00:12:41,496
I sent you a packet, okay?
See ya, buddy!
Love you!

162
00:12:41,574 --> 00:12:44,372
[ Beep ]
Sound good, Big Bird?

163
00:12:46,412 --> 00:12:49,813
You wanna go rafting
with my old college chums?

164
00:12:53,486 --> 00:12:55,818
Nice to see you too.

165
00:13:40,166 --> 00:13:42,828
[ Emily Chuckling ]
[ Joe ]
Why is that funny?

166
00:13:42,902 --> 00:13:45,370
I just don't picture you
with a beak, I guess.

167
00:13:45,438 --> 00:13:49,306
All right. Well,
just imagine soaring around
with me up there, flying.

168
00:13:49,375 --> 00:13:51,673
If you do,
you're on your own.
Why?

169
00:13:51,744 --> 00:13:55,145
Because eagles eat
bunny rabbits.
I'm a vegetarian.

170
00:13:55,214 --> 00:13:57,682
In your next life too?
Yes.

171
00:13:57,750 --> 00:14:01,709
You mean, if you got a chance
to come back, you'd want
to be earthbound again?

172
00:14:03,422 --> 00:14:06,949
No. I'll fly around
with you up there.

173
00:14:07,026 --> 00:14:09,392
But you know what
I'm gonna be.

174
00:14:10,763 --> 00:14:13,231
Yeah, but...

175
00:14:13,299 --> 00:14:16,234
if I'm a bird
and you're an insect,
Yeah?

176
00:14:16,302 --> 00:14:18,532
how are we gonna--

177
00:14:18,604 --> 00:14:21,630
You know.
You know.

178
00:14:21,707 --> 00:14:24,972
We'll just have to
do enough of that
in this lifetime...

179
00:14:25,044 --> 00:14:27,638
to make up
for the next ten.

180
00:14:40,893 --> 00:14:43,157
[ Moaning ]

181
00:15:01,314 --> 00:15:04,112
[ Moaning ]

182
00:15:20,132 --> 00:15:22,498
[ Emily's Voice ]
I'm going
because I have to,Joe.

183
00:15:22,568 --> 00:15:25,594
Because it's who I am,
who we are...

184
00:15:25,671 --> 00:15:27,764
what we dedicated
our lives to.

185
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:31,003
For God sakes, Emily,
you're pregnant.
We addressed this, Joe...

186
00:15:31,077 --> 00:15:33,011
when we first met...

187
00:15:33,079 --> 00:15:36,048
that we'd pack our kids
in on our backs
if we had to...

188
00:15:36,115 --> 00:15:38,208
to show them
what was important,
to teach them our values.

189
00:15:38,284 --> 00:15:42,152
It was naive, Emily,
all right? It was naive.

190
00:15:44,257 --> 00:15:46,225
Our values?

191
00:15:51,998 --> 00:15:54,831
I'm needed there, Joe...

192
00:15:54,900 --> 00:15:58,427
and I'm going.

193
00:15:58,504 --> 00:16:02,440
Whether you choose to
or not.

194
00:16:03,009 --> 00:16:04,442
[ Banging Sound ]

195
00:16:30,469 --> 00:16:32,596
[ Man ] So this thing
was a paperweight?
[ Joe ] Yes.

196
00:16:32,672 --> 00:16:35,163
It was a present I gave her
for Valentine's Day.

197
00:16:35,241 --> 00:16:38,677
Got to weigh half a pound,
and it was squarely--
I mean squarely--

198
00:16:38,744 --> 00:16:41,975
on the bedside table
when I went to sleep.

199
00:16:42,048 --> 00:16:45,279
So what are you saying?

200
00:16:45,351 --> 00:16:47,319
I don't know.

201
00:16:47,386 --> 00:16:50,287
Nothing, I guess.
Just that...

202
00:16:50,356 --> 00:16:53,985
dragonflies were sort of
her thing, you know,
like a personal totem.

203
00:16:54,060 --> 00:16:57,928
How lndians have buffalo heads
or tiger heads or hawks...

204
00:16:57,997 --> 00:17:01,262
hers was a dragonfly.

205
00:17:01,334 --> 00:17:05,293
She even had this small
birthmark on her shoulder
that kind of looked like one.

206
00:17:05,371 --> 00:17:07,532
Said her grandfather
had one too...

207
00:17:07,606 --> 00:17:11,201
on his--
on his butt, I think.

208
00:17:11,277 --> 00:17:14,440
It's called
familial hemangioma.

209
00:17:14,513 --> 00:17:17,107
I once skunked
an entire graduating class...

210
00:17:17,183 --> 00:17:19,344
by putting it
on a final exam.

211
00:17:22,021 --> 00:17:24,854
When she was alive,
I had to scour for
anything I could find...

212
00:17:24,924 --> 00:17:27,791
with a dragonfly on it
to buy her a present.

213
00:17:27,860 --> 00:17:32,524
Now? Now I see 'em
everywhere.

214
00:17:32,598 --> 00:17:37,092
There was one-- There was
one bouncing against
my office window yesterday.

215
00:17:37,169 --> 00:17:39,262
A real one.

216
00:17:39,338 --> 00:17:41,932
Last night a package arrived.
She had bought
over the lnternet...

217
00:17:42,007 --> 00:17:44,134
a mobile to put on
the baby's crib...

218
00:17:44,210 --> 00:17:46,974
of dragonflies.

219
00:17:47,046 --> 00:17:50,812
And then this thing last night
with the paperweight.

220
00:17:50,883 --> 00:17:53,374
You know what I think?

221
00:17:53,452 --> 00:17:57,252
I think you are literally
going buggy living
in that house.

222
00:17:57,323 --> 00:18:00,690
Yeah, you should move.
You're rummaging around
in an empty nursery.

223
00:18:00,760 --> 00:18:03,752
You're living with
a talking parrot
who won't even speak to you.

224
00:18:03,829 --> 00:18:06,855
Never would.
Never liked me.

225
00:18:06,932 --> 00:18:10,129
Would only talk
to Emily.

226
00:18:10,202 --> 00:18:13,729
She even taught it
to announce her arrival
when she came in the door.

227
00:18:16,075 --> 00:18:18,703
"Honey.
Honey, I'm home."

228
00:18:18,778 --> 00:18:21,212
You ought to sell
that thing, Joe.
Get rid of it.

229
00:18:22,681 --> 00:18:25,081
Stuck with it.

230
00:18:25,151 --> 00:18:28,143
I promised her
I'd keep it forever, and I'd
put a provision in my will...

231
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:31,587
that if anything ever happened
to me, someone I trusted
would take care of it.

232
00:18:33,225 --> 00:18:35,659
Would you?

233
00:18:35,728 --> 00:18:37,195
Would you?

234
00:18:37,229 --> 00:18:39,857
Oh, no.
It's your promise, buddy.
It's not mine.

235
00:18:43,035 --> 00:18:45,663
I need to live up to
my promises to her.

236
00:18:46,906 --> 00:18:49,340
That's one thing
I need to do.
Okay, fine.

237
00:18:51,210 --> 00:18:53,201
Any other promises
that I should know about?

238
00:18:53,279 --> 00:18:57,238
Just one, but I'm
taking care of that one
myself, starting...

239
00:18:57,316 --> 00:18:59,307
today.

240
00:18:59,385 --> 00:19:01,819
Hi, Joe.
Hugh.

241
00:19:01,887 --> 00:19:05,846
- I was kind of hoping you took
our conversation seriously.
- I did.

242
00:19:05,925 --> 00:19:09,554
I convinced Joe to take
a couple of months off,
with all that's happened.

243
00:19:09,628 --> 00:19:12,620
- Right,Joe?
- I promised Emily I'd
look in on her kids...

244
00:19:12,698 --> 00:19:16,031
on the oncology ward
while she was gone--
I never did.

245
00:19:16,101 --> 00:19:18,729
I thought this might be
a good day.

246
00:19:18,804 --> 00:19:22,296
After six months?
On oncology?

247
00:19:22,374 --> 00:19:26,140
I'm not sure how many
are left, but if it's
for Emily, fine.

248
00:19:29,548 --> 00:19:32,847
Asshole.
You should
get away, Joe.

249
00:19:32,918 --> 00:19:35,682
Isn't there someplace
you can go?

250
00:21:07,846 --> 00:21:10,212
[ Boy's Voice, Echoing ]
Joe!

251
00:21:28,334 --> 00:21:30,996
Joe!

252
00:21:47,853 --> 00:21:49,787
Joe!

253
00:21:53,492 --> 00:21:55,619
Joe!

254
00:21:55,694 --> 00:21:58,891
Joe, can't you hear me?
Joe!

255
00:21:58,964 --> 00:22:02,195
Joe!

256
00:22:06,372 --> 00:22:09,535
- All right. Hold C.P.R.
- I'm getting nothing.

257
00:22:09,608 --> 00:22:12,008
Continue it.
Shock him at 30.
Let me in there.

258
00:22:12,077 --> 00:22:15,979
Come on, Jeffrey.
Hang in there. Clear.
Keep it going.

259
00:22:16,048 --> 00:22:17,709
Still nothing.
Charging to 60.

260
00:22:17,783 --> 00:22:21,184
Shock him.
Clear.

261
00:22:21,253 --> 00:22:23,847
- Nothing.
- Go again.
- He's not responding.

262
00:22:23,922 --> 00:22:25,856
I said again.
There's no pulse at all.

263
00:22:25,924 --> 00:22:28,552
-He's not coming back this time.
-Damn it, do it again!

264
00:22:28,627 --> 00:22:30,219
Clear!

265
00:22:32,131 --> 00:22:35,157
[ Steady Beep ]

266
00:22:35,234 --> 00:22:38,397
[ Sighs ]
He's gone.

267
00:22:38,470 --> 00:22:42,167
[ Steady Beep Continues ]

268
00:23:04,430 --> 00:23:06,955
- [ Rhythmic Beep ]
- He's got a rhythm.

269
00:23:07,032 --> 00:23:09,364
- He's back! Jump on it!
- He's coming back!

270
00:23:09,435 --> 00:23:12,563
Yes, Jeffrey, yes!
Do you need to be here?

271
00:23:12,638 --> 00:23:15,436
Put that O-2 mask on him.
Clear the room, please.
Get me an E.K.G.

272
00:23:15,507 --> 00:23:18,943
You'll have to leave.
Don't let him pull out
that l.V. Jeffrey.

273
00:23:19,011 --> 00:23:23,311
Jeffrey, can you hear me?
Ah, pupils reactive.

274
00:23:23,382 --> 00:23:25,373
I just came on.
What happened?

275
00:23:25,451 --> 00:23:27,385
They're stabilizing him.

276
00:23:27,453 --> 00:23:31,480
He flat-lined,
and his heart started again.

277
00:23:31,557 --> 00:23:36,859
That's our Jeffrey. His heart
stopped more times than anyone
in the history of science.

278
00:23:36,929 --> 00:23:40,126
He'll come out of there
with all kinds of stories about
who he met in the tunnel...

279
00:23:40,199 --> 00:23:42,099
and what they said.

280
00:23:42,167 --> 00:23:44,465
[ Knocking ]

281
00:23:58,250 --> 00:24:00,411
Hi, I'm Dr. Darrow
from Emergency.

282
00:24:00,486 --> 00:24:02,351
I know who you are.

283
00:24:02,421 --> 00:24:06,517
The hospital administrator
heard that you got in the way
in l.C.U. yesterday...

284
00:24:06,592 --> 00:24:10,323
and asked to be notified
if you came back here
again.

285
00:24:10,395 --> 00:24:13,660
Did the boy who was being
resuscitated last night--

286
00:24:13,732 --> 00:24:15,996
Jeffrey--
Reardon.

287
00:24:16,068 --> 00:24:19,037
Right. Is he--
Is he still on the floor?

288
00:24:19,104 --> 00:24:22,198
Mm-hmm. He was one of
your wife's favorites.

289
00:24:22,274 --> 00:24:24,333
Actually,
that's why I'm here.

290
00:24:24,409 --> 00:24:28,311
I promised I'd look in
on her kids, but there
don't seem to be many left.

291
00:24:32,818 --> 00:24:36,254
Be great if you could
give me a little help,
maybe not...

292
00:24:36,321 --> 00:24:39,017
put in that call to
the hospital administrator.

293
00:24:40,659 --> 00:24:44,652
Between you and me, Doctor,
the hospital administrator is--

294
00:24:44,730 --> 00:24:46,664
how do I put it--

295
00:24:46,732 --> 00:24:48,893
I use the word "asshole."

296
00:24:48,967 --> 00:24:52,300
[ Chuckling ]
That about captures it.

297
00:24:53,705 --> 00:24:56,299
Three-one-five.
He's a real trip.

298
00:24:56,375 --> 00:24:58,866
You'll love him.
Thanks.

299
00:25:08,387 --> 00:25:11,185
- Hello.
- Hi.

300
00:25:11,256 --> 00:25:13,622
How's he doing?
Great.

301
00:25:16,695 --> 00:25:18,822
Nice.
What is it?

302
00:25:20,299 --> 00:25:22,927
I couldn't say.
Guess.

303
00:25:24,336 --> 00:25:26,270
All right.

304
00:25:28,207 --> 00:25:31,301
Crucifix made of Jell-O?

305
00:25:31,376 --> 00:25:34,607
Man, you're good.
He's good.

306
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:37,444
He hasn't stopped drawing
them since he got out
of the l.C.U. yesterday.

307
00:25:41,153 --> 00:25:43,087
So what is it?

308
00:25:43,155 --> 00:25:45,521
I don't know.
That's why I'm asking.

309
00:25:45,591 --> 00:25:47,582
Just woke up
thinking about it.

310
00:25:47,659 --> 00:25:50,457
I happened to be
in the l.C.U.
yesterday, Jeffrey.

311
00:25:50,529 --> 00:25:53,191
I know.
I saw you in there.

312
00:25:53,265 --> 00:25:55,529
You saw me in there?

313
00:25:55,601 --> 00:25:58,798
Yeah. You came in
through the back of the room
standing over my bed.

314
00:26:02,674 --> 00:26:05,165
You saw me
come over to your bed?

315
00:26:05,244 --> 00:26:08,873
Pretty sure it was you.
But the tie was different.

316
00:26:08,947 --> 00:26:11,074
Jeffrey!

317
00:26:11,149 --> 00:26:13,674
Could I ask--

318
00:26:13,752 --> 00:26:17,051
We're not encouraged
to discuss these things.

319
00:26:17,122 --> 00:26:20,990
There was a nun on the ward
interviewing kids who'd had
near-death experiences.

320
00:26:21,059 --> 00:26:23,653
Sister Madeline
from Chaplain Services.

321
00:26:23,729 --> 00:26:27,256
Stirred up all kinds of
trouble for the hospital
when some of it appeared...

322
00:26:27,332 --> 00:26:28,959
on a TV tabloid show.

323
00:26:29,034 --> 00:26:30,763
She never even
talked to me...

324
00:26:30,802 --> 00:26:33,737
and I've got the best
near-death experiences
of anyone.

325
00:26:35,374 --> 00:26:39,367
I'm allowed a coffee break
if there's a doctor with him.

326
00:26:39,444 --> 00:26:42,641
In spite of hospital policy,
I think they need to talk
about it.

327
00:26:44,983 --> 00:26:48,077
You're scheduled for
a CAT scan, Jeffrey.
Don't go without me.

328
00:26:58,497 --> 00:27:00,931
So what are we talking
about here, Jeffrey?

329
00:27:00,999 --> 00:27:04,264
What we shouldn't.

330
00:27:04,336 --> 00:27:07,066
In the l.C.U. yesterday,
when I approached your bed...

331
00:27:07,139 --> 00:27:09,539
it seemed to me
you were pretty--

332
00:27:09,608 --> 00:27:12,907
- I was flat-lined.
- Exactly.

333
00:27:12,978 --> 00:27:16,880
So how could you
look up and see me?
Couldn't.

334
00:27:16,949 --> 00:27:19,975
- But you said--
- I looked down.

335
00:27:20,052 --> 00:27:21,986
You looked down?

336
00:27:22,054 --> 00:27:25,455
From the ceiling.
That's where I was
when I saw you.

337
00:27:30,462 --> 00:27:32,396
Okay.

338
00:27:32,464 --> 00:27:34,523
Don't believe me?

339
00:27:34,599 --> 00:27:36,362
Should l?

340
00:27:37,736 --> 00:27:39,897
Ever see that little
bald spot on top of your head?

341
00:27:42,708 --> 00:27:44,642
Bend down here.

342
00:27:44,710 --> 00:27:46,837
Come on.
Bend down here.

343
00:27:48,947 --> 00:27:51,677
Yeah, that was you.
[ Giggling ]

344
00:27:55,754 --> 00:27:58,450
Jeffrey,
do you know my name?

345
00:27:58,523 --> 00:28:02,254
You look like a--
a William to me.

346
00:28:02,327 --> 00:28:04,318
I'm a Joe.

347
00:28:04,396 --> 00:28:06,330
Does it ring a bell?

348
00:28:09,234 --> 00:28:11,168
Emily's Joe?

349
00:28:13,205 --> 00:28:15,139
Joe Darrow.

350
00:28:17,809 --> 00:28:20,369
I saw her yesterday too.

351
00:28:20,445 --> 00:28:23,414
What do you mean,
Jeffrey, you saw her?

352
00:28:23,482 --> 00:28:26,110
She was there.

353
00:28:27,486 --> 00:28:29,716
Where?

354
00:28:29,788 --> 00:28:31,722
All around me.

355
00:28:34,226 --> 00:28:36,888
Inside the rainbow.

356
00:28:36,962 --> 00:28:40,489
The mist.
I was falling...

357
00:28:40,565 --> 00:28:42,533
falling through it...

358
00:28:44,069 --> 00:28:46,469
until she caught me...

359
00:28:46,538 --> 00:28:48,472
then brought me
back up.

360
00:28:49,775 --> 00:28:51,902
She kind of flew me.

361
00:28:51,977 --> 00:28:54,775
She flew me out...

362
00:28:56,982 --> 00:28:59,075
so I could come back...

363
00:29:00,685 --> 00:29:02,949
and tell somebody something.

364
00:29:03,021 --> 00:29:05,319
Tell what, Jeffrey?

365
00:29:06,458 --> 00:29:08,050
To who?

366
00:29:10,829 --> 00:29:12,922
Joe.

367
00:29:14,332 --> 00:29:16,163
Tell me what, Jeffrey?

368
00:29:18,236 --> 00:29:20,170
Tell Joe what?

369
00:29:21,640 --> 00:29:23,938
It was loud in the rainbow...

370
00:29:24,009 --> 00:29:25,943
Iike thunder in there.

371
00:29:26,011 --> 00:29:30,243
- Tell me what, Jeffrey?
- I don't know.

372
00:29:30,315 --> 00:29:32,749
You were calling my name.

373
00:29:32,818 --> 00:29:35,548
Joe.

374
00:29:35,620 --> 00:29:38,418
Joe!

375
00:29:38,490 --> 00:29:40,424
Joe, can't you hear me?

376
00:29:40,492 --> 00:29:43,017
Joe!
All right, Jeffrey.

377
00:29:43,095 --> 00:29:46,553
Joe! Joe!
Jeffrey, slow down.

378
00:29:46,631 --> 00:29:48,861
Whoa, whoa.

379
00:29:48,934 --> 00:29:51,926
Look at my eyes.
Look at my eyes.

380
00:29:52,003 --> 00:29:53,937
Just breathe.

381
00:29:54,005 --> 00:29:56,132
Just breathe
a little bit, okay?

382
00:29:57,375 --> 00:29:59,309
What happened?

383
00:29:59,377 --> 00:30:01,572
I'm fine.
We were--

384
00:30:01,646 --> 00:30:04,444
He wanted to know
what happened yesterday.

385
00:30:04,516 --> 00:30:07,314
His heart stopped again.
I know.

386
00:30:07,385 --> 00:30:10,320
- I was there, actually.
- He wanted to know
what happened...

387
00:30:10,388 --> 00:30:12,322
while it was stopped.

388
00:30:12,390 --> 00:30:14,858
Oh. Telling one of
his tall tales again.

389
00:30:14,926 --> 00:30:16,860
Trying to get on TV.

390
00:30:16,928 --> 00:30:20,295
I'm gonna give him a dust mop
next time so he can sweep
the ceiling while he's up there.

391
00:30:20,365 --> 00:30:22,663
My daddy don't believe me.

392
00:30:23,768 --> 00:30:25,736
He do the "bald spot"
on you?

393
00:30:29,074 --> 00:30:31,372
[ Laughing ]

394
00:30:31,443 --> 00:30:33,377
It don't work
on everybody.

395
00:30:33,445 --> 00:30:37,506
Just us bald guys, huh?
Phew! Yeah, he got me
with that one too.

396
00:30:40,652 --> 00:30:43,883
You had me going there,
Jeffrey.
It was the truth.

397
00:30:43,955 --> 00:30:45,980
You don't believe me?

398
00:30:46,057 --> 00:30:49,151
[ Woman Over P.A., lndistinct ]

399
00:30:51,329 --> 00:30:54,423
What if I do remember what
she wants to tell you...

400
00:30:54,499 --> 00:30:57,161
then would you believe me?

401
00:30:57,235 --> 00:30:59,203
Do you remember it?

402
00:30:59,271 --> 00:31:02,069
If you come back, I might.

403
00:31:02,140 --> 00:31:04,074
[ Father ]
What who wants to tell him?

404
00:31:04,142 --> 00:31:07,543
[ Jeffrey ]
His wife. She wants me
to tell him something.

405
00:31:07,612 --> 00:31:11,207
Probably to take
out the trash, huh?
[ Chuckles ]

406
00:31:53,558 --> 00:31:55,958
[ Woman Chuckling ]
[ Man ]
What?

407
00:31:56,027 --> 00:31:58,359
[ Joe ]
He even had me believing
he saw my bald spot...

408
00:31:58,430 --> 00:32:01,399
from the ceiling,
till I saw a mirror
behind my head.

409
00:32:01,466 --> 00:32:04,026
[ Man ]
We can thank Mom for those
genes, right, Dad?

410
00:32:04,102 --> 00:32:07,629
I hate to burst your bubble,
Joe, but I can see
your bald spot from here.

411
00:32:07,706 --> 00:32:10,675
I think bald is sexy.

412
00:32:10,742 --> 00:32:12,676
Really?
Yes.

413
00:32:12,744 --> 00:32:14,678
I've got a parrot
that might turn you on.

414
00:32:14,746 --> 00:32:17,715
Are you still
living with that
messy thing? Joe!

415
00:32:17,782 --> 00:32:20,876
We're working on
our relationship.
Is it a talking parrot?

416
00:32:20,952 --> 00:32:23,386
A listening parrot.

417
00:32:23,455 --> 00:32:27,016
A bird after my own heart.
That's what I do
for a living: listen.

418
00:32:27,092 --> 00:32:29,026
Really?

419
00:32:29,094 --> 00:32:33,463
Gwyn's a grief counselor, Joe.
That's why I thought it might
be a good idea for you to meet.

420
00:32:36,768 --> 00:32:38,702
Is that right?

421
00:32:38,770 --> 00:32:43,104
I've heard a lot of clients talk
about the near-death experiences
of their loved ones--

422
00:32:43,174 --> 00:32:45,506
how they'd wake up talking
about being in a dark tunnel...

423
00:32:45,577 --> 00:32:47,511
moving toward the light.

424
00:32:47,579 --> 00:32:49,570
And what's
your thought on it?

425
00:32:49,648 --> 00:32:53,414
I'm just your parrot,
Joe. Just listening.

426
00:32:53,485 --> 00:32:56,977
[ Man ] I can tell you
as an eye surgeon,
it's all very simple.

427
00:32:57,055 --> 00:32:59,615
The tunnel is
literal tunnel vision.

428
00:32:59,691 --> 00:33:02,421
And the white light
is the gradual bleaching out
of the optic screen.

429
00:33:02,494 --> 00:33:04,860
As it grows bigger,
it would seem like
you're moving toward it.

430
00:33:04,929 --> 00:33:07,659
How do you explain
their ability to recall
what everyone said...

431
00:33:07,732 --> 00:33:10,166
around their deathbed after
they were declared dead--

432
00:33:10,235 --> 00:33:12,362
to describe what
the doctors were wearing...

433
00:33:12,437 --> 00:33:14,803
down to the patterns
on their ties?

434
00:33:14,873 --> 00:33:17,171
[ Man ]
It's the way
we measure death.

435
00:33:17,242 --> 00:33:21,372
Obviously the brain
is still functioning
on some subliminal level...

436
00:33:21,446 --> 00:33:25,177
soaking up all the last bits
of what's left to hear and see.

437
00:33:25,250 --> 00:33:28,378
That's what you get
for having dinner
with a family of doctors--

438
00:33:28,453 --> 00:33:30,387
no discussion about
floating around
on the ceiling;

439
00:33:30,455 --> 00:33:32,650
no tunnel;
no bright lights.

440
00:33:32,724 --> 00:33:35,158
Next thing, they're gonna
tell us there's no tooth fairy.

441
00:33:38,830 --> 00:33:41,958
Funny thing is,
I thought I heard him
calling out for me.

442
00:33:42,033 --> 00:33:44,297
This kid.

443
00:33:44,369 --> 00:33:47,236
I heard his voice
calling 'Joe. "

444
00:33:48,907 --> 00:33:52,502
And when I introduced myself
to him, he asked me
if I was Emily's Joe.

445
00:33:54,179 --> 00:33:56,909
Said that Emily
was trying to reach me.

446
00:33:59,551 --> 00:34:02,611
Do you believe
she's trying to
reach you, Joe?

447
00:34:04,856 --> 00:34:07,450
No, Counselor, I don't.

448
00:34:12,097 --> 00:34:14,588
I can give you
an hour for free.

449
00:34:18,803 --> 00:34:21,795
Bye, Joe. You want me to
package up dessert for you?

450
00:34:21,873 --> 00:34:23,807
Sorry.
Use your phone?

451
00:34:30,415 --> 00:34:32,576
Excuse me.

452
00:34:38,923 --> 00:34:41,323
I am kind of busy
at the moment, yeah.

453
00:34:42,761 --> 00:34:45,389
Well, isn't there anyone else
who can cover for me tonight?

454
00:34:45,463 --> 00:34:48,432
All right. I understand.
I'll be right over.

455
00:34:51,669 --> 00:34:54,297
I'm sorry.
I'd really like to stay.
No, you wouldn't.

456
00:34:54,372 --> 00:34:56,306
It's too threatening.

457
00:34:56,374 --> 00:34:59,810
It's about unresolved issues
you're not ready
to deal with yet--

458
00:34:59,878 --> 00:35:02,870
guilt, anger
toward our loved ones--

459
00:35:02,947 --> 00:35:05,040
that's why
we conjure up spirits--

460
00:35:05,116 --> 00:35:07,141
from the Virgin Mary
to our dearly departed--

461
00:35:07,218 --> 00:35:11,279
because we need to
talk to them,
not the other way around.

462
00:35:12,457 --> 00:35:14,391
[ Scoffs ]

463
00:35:18,096 --> 00:35:21,361
You asked if I thought
she was trying to contact me,
and I never answered.

464
00:35:21,433 --> 00:35:23,492
Let me answer now.

465
00:35:23,568 --> 00:35:25,934
She was my
ultimate partner...

466
00:35:26,004 --> 00:35:29,906
my best friend and lover,
and I miss her
beyond belief.

467
00:35:29,974 --> 00:35:33,569
I also know I'm never
gonna see her again.

468
00:35:33,645 --> 00:35:35,579
Not ever.

469
00:35:35,647 --> 00:35:38,013
And I'm just beginning to
understand what that means
so intensely...

470
00:35:38,082 --> 00:35:40,744
that I sometimes wish that
I didn't have to wake up
anymore.

471
00:35:40,819 --> 00:35:43,481
And the last thing I need
is someone telling me
what to feel...

472
00:35:43,555 --> 00:35:45,489
or how to feel.

473
00:35:45,557 --> 00:35:47,821
Anger, yeah.

474
00:35:47,892 --> 00:35:50,156
Guilt, you bet.

475
00:35:50,228 --> 00:35:54,130
But I don't need you crawling
up my ass with a flashlight
to tell me about it.

476
00:35:54,199 --> 00:35:56,861
Keep going, Joe.
This is what you need.

477
00:35:58,136 --> 00:36:00,366
I'll drop you
a check in the mail.

478
00:36:27,198 --> 00:36:30,099
Hi.

479
00:36:30,168 --> 00:36:33,604
Hey.
What's your name?

480
00:36:33,671 --> 00:36:35,605
Ben.

481
00:36:35,673 --> 00:36:39,404
I'm Joe, Ben.
I know.

482
00:36:42,614 --> 00:36:44,946
Just admiring your artwork.

483
00:36:45,016 --> 00:36:47,450
What is it?

484
00:36:47,519 --> 00:36:50,420
She said you should
go there.

485
00:36:50,488 --> 00:36:52,422
I'm sorry?

486
00:36:52,490 --> 00:36:56,586
The lady.
The lady in the picture
down the hall.

487
00:36:56,661 --> 00:36:59,255
She said you'd...

488
00:36:59,330 --> 00:37:01,491
be coming to see me.

489
00:37:03,635 --> 00:37:07,799
- The nurse?
- They said she was
a doctor here.

490
00:37:11,342 --> 00:37:13,776
What doctor?

491
00:37:13,845 --> 00:37:17,804
- She wants you to go there.
- Go where?

492
00:37:28,726 --> 00:37:32,059
I'm not--
I'm not sure
what you mean, Ben.

493
00:37:32,130 --> 00:37:34,098
Go where?

494
00:37:35,466 --> 00:37:37,525
I dreamed of her...

495
00:37:37,602 --> 00:37:40,833
in the ambulance
when I came here.

496
00:37:40,905 --> 00:37:45,365
Then... I saw
her picture in the hall.

497
00:37:45,443 --> 00:37:48,173
You know,
the lady doctor?

498
00:37:48,246 --> 00:37:52,945
In the picture
of the Easter party,
with the cake on her nose?

499
00:37:53,017 --> 00:37:55,952
Are you talking
about Dr. Darrow?

500
00:37:58,289 --> 00:38:00,257
She died, I guess.

501
00:38:03,795 --> 00:38:05,990
And you dreamed of her?

502
00:38:10,501 --> 00:38:13,197
She wants you
to go there.

503
00:38:16,140 --> 00:38:18,165
Go where, Ben?

504
00:38:19,377 --> 00:38:21,811
The rainbow.

505
00:38:23,815 --> 00:38:25,942
That's a rainbow?

506
00:38:28,152 --> 00:38:31,315
This--
This is a rainbow?

507
00:38:41,466 --> 00:38:43,832
Have we met before, Ben?

508
00:38:45,603 --> 00:38:47,537
I don't know.

509
00:38:49,741 --> 00:38:52,175
How do you know
who I am?

510
00:38:53,845 --> 00:38:57,144
She showed me your face.

511
00:39:01,419 --> 00:39:03,353
In a picture?

512
00:39:05,857 --> 00:39:07,791
In my mind.

513
00:39:09,027 --> 00:39:12,827
She said
I have to come back...

514
00:39:12,897 --> 00:39:14,922
to tell you to go there.

515
00:39:18,603 --> 00:39:20,594
To a rainbow?

516
00:39:23,841 --> 00:39:25,775
Yes.

517
00:39:28,513 --> 00:39:32,643
Well, how would l--
How would I do that, Ben?

518
00:39:49,333 --> 00:39:52,268
Christine,
the boy in 312--
Ben?

519
00:39:52,336 --> 00:39:54,497
Yes.
Did he know my wife?

520
00:39:54,572 --> 00:39:58,599
I don't think so.
I think he just
came in two weeks ago.

521
00:39:58,676 --> 00:40:01,577
Yeah. On the third
in a coma.
Septic shock.

522
00:40:01,646 --> 00:40:04,137
Why, Joe?

523
00:40:06,684 --> 00:40:08,618
Nothing.

524
00:40:10,121 --> 00:40:12,112
Miriam--

525
00:40:12,190 --> 00:40:14,886
The first kid,
he calls my name...

526
00:40:14,959 --> 00:40:17,223
I follow him in
to the l.C.U....

527
00:40:17,295 --> 00:40:19,991
where he flat-lines,
dies.

528
00:40:20,064 --> 00:40:24,023
Then when he's resuscitated,
says he saw me while he's
floating around the ceiling.

529
00:40:24,102 --> 00:40:26,764
And that Emily--
who he met in a rainbow--

530
00:40:26,838 --> 00:40:28,999
sent him back
to tell me something.

531
00:40:29,073 --> 00:40:31,439
Tell you what?

532
00:40:31,509 --> 00:40:35,036
He doesn't remember.
But the next kid does.

533
00:40:35,113 --> 00:40:37,308
You want jelly?
I got two kinds.

534
00:40:37,381 --> 00:40:40,646
Are you taking me seriously?
Yes.
Is strawberry okay?

535
00:40:40,718 --> 00:40:44,154
What does it matter?
Do you-- Do you hear
what I'm telling you?

536
00:40:44,222 --> 00:40:47,316
I'm just trying to focus
on something real here, Joe.

537
00:40:47,391 --> 00:40:50,986
And you think this isn't?
Doesn't sound it so far.

538
00:40:54,665 --> 00:40:56,599
Listen to me, Joe.

539
00:40:59,604 --> 00:41:03,904
After Hannah died, l--
I saw her everywhere.

540
00:41:03,975 --> 00:41:06,671
She told me I know
she was watching over me...

541
00:41:06,744 --> 00:41:10,339
if I saw a daisy growing
out of the ground with all
the petals missing except one.

542
00:41:10,414 --> 00:41:13,406
We used to play
"She Loves Me,
She Loves Me Not. "

543
00:41:13,484 --> 00:41:18,512
And one day,
I saw an entire field
of one-petaled daisies.

544
00:41:18,589 --> 00:41:21,581
Well, there you go.
How do you explain that?

545
00:41:21,659 --> 00:41:25,254
I was delusional.
Well, I'm not, okay?

546
00:41:25,329 --> 00:41:27,559
I had these conversations.

547
00:41:27,632 --> 00:41:30,658
Aren't you the guy that
doesn't believe in heaven?

548
00:41:30,735 --> 00:41:33,704
This isn't heaven.
This is rainbows.

549
00:41:33,771 --> 00:41:38,708
Oh. And she wants you
to join her
inside a rainbow?

550
00:41:39,844 --> 00:41:41,937
According to these kids,
that's accurate.

551
00:41:42,013 --> 00:41:45,005
Well, according to me,
they're putting you on.

552
00:41:45,082 --> 00:41:48,279
So you think
they're lying.
I'm a lawyer, Joe.

553
00:41:48,352 --> 00:41:51,287
Nothing is real
without evidence.

554
00:41:51,355 --> 00:41:54,847
Have you personally had
any experience with Emily
since her death?

555
00:41:54,926 --> 00:41:56,894
And if so,
has it been documented?

556
00:41:56,961 --> 00:41:59,953
- You know the answer.
Of course I haven't.
- And why haven't you?

557
00:42:00,031 --> 00:42:02,329
Because I haven't gone
halfway to heaven...

558
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:05,426
and she has no way
of reaching me.

559
00:42:19,350 --> 00:42:21,614
It does sound nuts,
doesn't it?

560
00:42:21,686 --> 00:42:25,645
Well, I wouldn't employ you
in my hospital
if I heard that.

561
00:42:25,723 --> 00:42:28,886
And if I were you,
I'd stay away from there.

562
00:42:28,960 --> 00:42:31,724
Isn't there somewhere
you can go?

563
00:42:33,764 --> 00:42:35,823
I could go
on a white-water trip.

564
00:42:36,901 --> 00:42:38,869
Just what I've always
wanted to see--

565
00:42:40,171 --> 00:42:42,935
white water.
I'll take care
of Big Bird.

566
00:42:43,007 --> 00:42:45,475
Get out of here.

567
00:42:45,543 --> 00:42:47,943
Go see white water...

568
00:42:48,012 --> 00:42:50,139
and get your head straight.

569
00:43:34,725 --> 00:43:36,659
Wanna see?

570
00:43:39,330 --> 00:43:41,958
They were the last thing
she sent us.

571
00:43:58,215 --> 00:44:01,343
Hmm.

572
00:44:01,419 --> 00:44:03,887
Sorry to break it
to you, pal, but, uh...

573
00:44:06,223 --> 00:44:08,157
she was cheatin' on ya.

574
00:44:28,779 --> 00:44:31,213
[ Wings Fluttering ]

575
00:44:38,889 --> 00:44:40,914
[ Fluttering Continues ]

576
00:44:47,398 --> 00:44:49,764
It's just a bug, Big Bird.

577
00:44:50,968 --> 00:44:53,596
Attracted to the light.

578
00:44:53,671 --> 00:44:56,105
Let's not get crazy here.

579
00:45:27,471 --> 00:45:30,907
[ Fluttering Resumes ]

580
00:45:36,881 --> 00:45:39,509
[ Big Bird ]
Honey, I'm home.

581
00:45:43,354 --> 00:45:45,686
Honey, I'm home.

582
00:46:40,711 --> 00:46:42,406
[ Squawks ]

583
00:46:44,248 --> 00:46:47,046
[ Squawking Continues ]

584
00:46:48,219 --> 00:46:49,914
Big Bird!

585
00:46:55,726 --> 00:46:58,695
Big Bird, no!

586
00:47:27,858 --> 00:47:29,849
[ Gasps ]

587
00:47:40,337 --> 00:47:43,500
[ Cell Phone Ringing ]
[ Miriam ]
Hello?

588
00:47:43,574 --> 00:47:45,508
[ Joe ] Miriam?
Joe?

589
00:47:45,576 --> 00:47:48,739
Miriam, listen to me.
The bird, it's sick.

590
00:47:48,812 --> 00:47:51,872
I had to leave it.
I'm on my way
to the hospital.

591
00:47:51,949 --> 00:47:55,146
- Are you okay?
- Actually, I'm not.

592
00:47:55,219 --> 00:47:57,949
I feel--

593
00:47:58,022 --> 00:48:00,286
I feel like
I'm losing my mind.

594
00:48:00,357 --> 00:48:02,450
What can I do?

595
00:48:02,526 --> 00:48:05,495
It was acting
like it used to
when she'd come home.

596
00:48:05,563 --> 00:48:08,361
I felt like she was there...

597
00:48:08,432 --> 00:48:10,696
in the house.

598
00:48:10,768 --> 00:48:13,236
Jesus, Joe.

599
00:48:13,304 --> 00:48:16,432
I don't know what to do
about the--
The bird?

600
00:48:16,507 --> 00:48:18,907
I'll take care of it.

601
00:48:18,976 --> 00:48:21,774
I'll wake up the vet
if I have to.

602
00:48:21,845 --> 00:48:24,575
You just...
hang in there, okay?

603
00:48:24,648 --> 00:48:26,582
All right. Thanks.

604
00:48:26,650 --> 00:48:29,244
[ Line Clicks ]

605
00:48:31,822 --> 00:48:34,120
Is Jeffrey awake?
Not a good idea
right now.

606
00:48:34,191 --> 00:48:37,991
Is he in his room?
Visiting hours aren't
until 10.:00,Joe.

607
00:48:38,062 --> 00:48:39,996
Joe!

608
00:48:41,799 --> 00:48:43,733
Joe.

609
00:48:53,744 --> 00:48:57,077
Joe, there was some talk
around here I think
you should know about.

610
00:48:57,147 --> 00:48:59,638
Where is he?
Jeffrey?

611
00:48:59,717 --> 00:49:02,015
He's downstairs
getting blood work,
but can I tell you what l--

612
00:49:02,086 --> 00:49:04,520
His nurse-- Is she with him?
Would you just listen
to me for a minute?

613
00:49:04,588 --> 00:49:06,556
She said there was
a nun on the ward...

614
00:49:06,624 --> 00:49:09,115
interviewing kids about
near-death experiences.

615
00:49:09,193 --> 00:49:11,661
Sister Madeline.
Do you know
where she is?

616
00:49:11,729 --> 00:49:14,129
She's no longer
employed here,Joe.

617
00:49:14,198 --> 00:49:16,132
And you know why?

618
00:49:16,200 --> 00:49:18,668
Because she overstepped
her bounds.

619
00:49:18,736 --> 00:49:20,829
Where is she employed?

620
00:49:20,904 --> 00:49:23,168
Would-- Would
Chaplain Services know?

621
00:49:23,240 --> 00:49:25,902
Could you leave us
alone for a minute?

622
00:49:25,976 --> 00:49:28,240
[ Woman Over P.A.,
lndistinct ]

623
00:49:32,783 --> 00:49:35,115
What are you doing,
Joe?

624
00:49:35,185 --> 00:49:37,983
You know
what I'm doing.
You gave me permission--

625
00:49:38,055 --> 00:49:41,821
To look in on Emily's kids.
That was two days ago,
and you haven't left since.

626
00:49:41,892 --> 00:49:43,985
I told you,
I promised my wife.

627
00:49:44,061 --> 00:49:45,995
That you'd upset them?

628
00:49:46,063 --> 00:49:49,829
Jeffrey's cardiologist saw
the readout on his E.K.G.
from 2:30 yesterday afternoon...

629
00:49:49,900 --> 00:49:52,198
and he was damned upset
that your visit...

630
00:49:52,269 --> 00:49:54,499
put him under
that kind of stress.

631
00:49:54,571 --> 00:49:56,539
What is going on, Joe?

632
00:50:05,683 --> 00:50:07,651
The bird's okay.

633
00:50:07,718 --> 00:50:09,913
He will outlive us all.

634
00:50:09,987 --> 00:50:12,785
I tried to clean up
some of the mess in there--

635
00:50:12,856 --> 00:50:15,450
overturned lamp,
broken vase.

636
00:50:15,526 --> 00:50:17,926
You didn't have to
do all that.

637
00:50:17,995 --> 00:50:19,724
I didn't do all that.

638
00:50:19,797 --> 00:50:23,392
I left some of it...
to discuss with you.

639
00:50:27,304 --> 00:50:30,398
That weird picture
you told me
the kids were drawing?

640
00:50:30,474 --> 00:50:32,738
The wiggly cross?

641
00:50:36,914 --> 00:50:39,405
Is it the kids
drawing it,Joe?

642
00:50:39,483 --> 00:50:42,316
Or is it you?

643
00:50:46,123 --> 00:50:49,092
'Cause if you did this,
you need some help.

644
00:50:51,829 --> 00:50:54,229
It's all over
the windows too.

645
00:51:04,541 --> 00:51:07,305
Watch the bird for me,
will you?

646
00:51:13,917 --> 00:51:16,112
[ Playful Chattering ]

647
00:51:39,743 --> 00:51:41,802
Excuse me.

648
00:51:41,879 --> 00:51:44,609
Excuse me. I'm looking
for Sister Madeline.
Is that--

649
00:51:44,681 --> 00:51:47,980
May I ask
what this is about?
It's personal. Is that her?

650
00:51:48,051 --> 00:51:51,282
- You'll have to call the office
for an appointment.
- Excuse me!

651
00:51:51,355 --> 00:51:54,017
- Sir. Sir!
- Sister Madeline?

652
00:51:54,091 --> 00:51:56,355
Sister Madeline,
could I speak to you?

653
00:51:56,427 --> 00:51:59,863
Sir!
Please.
Sister Madeline?

654
00:52:01,532 --> 00:52:04,057
Please,
are you Sis--

655
00:52:04,134 --> 00:52:06,864
Please.
Are you Sister Madeline?

656
00:52:06,937 --> 00:52:09,337
This is private property.
You are trespassing.

657
00:52:09,406 --> 00:52:11,601
I know, I tried to call.
I'm sorry.

658
00:52:11,675 --> 00:52:13,939
Chaplain Services only
gave me an address.

659
00:52:14,011 --> 00:52:16,639
He'll call the police.
Please--

660
00:52:16,713 --> 00:52:18,647
Just five minutes.

661
00:52:18,715 --> 00:52:21,081
You people have done
enough damage.

662
00:52:21,151 --> 00:52:24,120
- You don't understand.
- You don't.

663
00:52:24,188 --> 00:52:26,884
No more journalists.
No more interviews.

664
00:52:26,957 --> 00:52:30,120
I'm not a journalist.
I'm a-- I'm a doctor.

665
00:52:31,395 --> 00:52:33,693
Head of Emergency Services...

666
00:52:33,764 --> 00:52:36,528
at Chicago
Memorial Hospital.

667
00:52:36,600 --> 00:52:38,397
Joe Darrow.

668
00:52:41,104 --> 00:52:43,834
Emily's Joe.
Yes.

669
00:52:46,944 --> 00:52:48,935
[ Whispering ]
That's why I need
to talk to you.

670
00:52:49,012 --> 00:52:51,412
I need to know
about your work.

671
00:52:53,750 --> 00:52:56,480
I've called the police.
I'd advise you to leave.

672
00:52:56,520 --> 00:52:59,785
It's all right.
He's not a journalist.
He's still trespassing.

673
00:52:59,857 --> 00:53:02,690
I'm sorry.
We agreed to hire
Sister Madeline...

674
00:53:02,759 --> 00:53:06,627
with the understanding
that her presence here
wouldn't cause any disturbances.

675
00:53:06,697 --> 00:53:09,131
[ Bell Ringing ]
Sister.

676
00:53:09,199 --> 00:53:11,360
Yes, sir.

677
00:53:17,274 --> 00:53:20,175
The police respond quickly.
I'd advise you to leave.

678
00:53:39,096 --> 00:53:41,894
Do you have business
at the school, sir?

679
00:53:41,965 --> 00:53:45,059
Beg your pardon?
Step over here,
please.

680
00:53:49,306 --> 00:53:52,173
[ Police Radio Chatter ]

681
00:54:33,050 --> 00:54:36,918
[ Sister Madeline ]
And I realized that in an age
where no one believes...

682
00:54:36,987 --> 00:54:41,890
in miracles anymore,
I was witnessing miracles
every day.

683
00:54:41,959 --> 00:54:45,053
And the pediatric
oncology ward...

684
00:54:45,128 --> 00:54:48,461
was the perfect laboratory
to study it--

685
00:54:48,532 --> 00:54:50,966
the near-death experience.

686
00:54:51,034 --> 00:54:55,334
Being kids, they were
more open to what happens...

687
00:54:55,405 --> 00:54:58,033
on the other side.

688
00:54:58,108 --> 00:55:01,703
You're convinced it's not
just in their minds?

689
00:55:01,778 --> 00:55:04,679
Just in their minds?

690
00:55:06,183 --> 00:55:10,745
What we're experiencing
right now could be
just in your mind.

691
00:55:10,821 --> 00:55:13,722
You're a doctor
because you dreamed...

692
00:55:13,790 --> 00:55:16,623
of being one, right?

693
00:55:16,693 --> 00:55:20,390
You imagined that...

694
00:55:20,464 --> 00:55:22,955
for yourself.

695
00:55:23,033 --> 00:55:26,833
If we can create this world
with what we imagine...

696
00:55:26,903 --> 00:55:29,235
why not the next?

697
00:55:29,306 --> 00:55:32,070
S-So you're saying,
belief--

698
00:55:32,142 --> 00:55:34,576
Gets us there.

699
00:55:34,645 --> 00:55:36,943
Did Emily believe?

700
00:55:38,882 --> 00:55:41,908
Because I think
she got there.

701
00:55:41,985 --> 00:55:45,477
I believe she's trying
to contact me.

702
00:55:45,555 --> 00:55:48,217
Two kids have seen her.

703
00:55:48,291 --> 00:55:52,125
One was flat-lined,
another in a coma.

704
00:55:52,195 --> 00:55:55,494
In the tunnel?
ln a rainbow.

705
00:55:55,565 --> 00:55:58,363
Trying to tell me something,
something urgent.

706
00:55:59,569 --> 00:56:01,833
But I don't know what.

707
00:56:01,905 --> 00:56:06,103
And they-- they--
they draw this...

708
00:56:06,176 --> 00:56:09,509
after they've--
after they've seen her.

709
00:56:09,579 --> 00:56:13,447
Have you ever seen
this before?

710
00:56:13,517 --> 00:56:15,451
No.

711
00:56:25,562 --> 00:56:27,496
I don't know.

712
00:56:27,564 --> 00:56:32,263
Am l--
Am I just going nuts?

713
00:56:34,471 --> 00:56:37,201
As nuts
as Christopher Columbus...

714
00:56:37,274 --> 00:56:40,072
thinking there was
another side to the earth.

715
00:56:42,412 --> 00:56:45,347
Talk to an anesthesiologist.
They'll tell you.

716
00:56:45,415 --> 00:56:49,078
There are a hundred steps on
the ladder of consciousness...

717
00:56:49,152 --> 00:56:52,087
between being
fully alert...

718
00:56:52,155 --> 00:56:54,385
and being dead.

719
00:56:54,458 --> 00:56:57,450
To put a patient under,
they bring them down...

720
00:56:57,527 --> 00:57:00,189
only to the tenth rung.

721
00:57:00,263 --> 00:57:05,132
Beneath that is
a descending gray scale...

722
00:57:05,202 --> 00:57:07,534
Iike the depths
of an ocean...

723
00:57:07,604 --> 00:57:10,368
no one has explored.

724
00:57:10,440 --> 00:57:14,467
It's in those depths,
those murky depths...

725
00:57:14,544 --> 00:57:17,240
she's finding them--
the children.

726
00:57:17,314 --> 00:57:20,306
They're her conduit,
because she knew...

727
00:57:20,383 --> 00:57:22,908
you'd find your way
to them.

728
00:57:24,521 --> 00:57:26,751
Stay close to them.

729
00:57:26,823 --> 00:57:29,849
Be with them when they slip away
so you can be with them...

730
00:57:29,926 --> 00:57:33,794
when they first awaken,
before the details fade.

731
00:57:35,165 --> 00:57:37,258
One of them...

732
00:57:37,334 --> 00:57:40,770
will come back
with the answer.

733
00:58:42,098 --> 00:58:45,898
[ Elevator Bell Dings ]
[ Man ] Careful. Careful.
Okay, let's go. Sit back!

734
00:58:45,969 --> 00:58:47,834
Release forms.
I'll get it.

735
00:58:47,904 --> 00:58:50,839
[ Chattering ]

736
00:58:50,907 --> 00:58:53,102
- Where is it?
- Down the right.
- Careful with the transfer.

737
00:58:53,176 --> 00:58:55,110
Watch your line here.
Keep it pumping.
Right here.

738
00:58:55,178 --> 00:58:57,772
Hook him up to the ventilator
when you get inside.
I'll get the monitor.

739
00:58:57,848 --> 00:59:00,510
This is Jeanette in Nephrology.
I need to speak
to Dr. Dickinson, please.

740
00:59:00,584 --> 00:59:02,518
Monitors are ready.
Dr. Darrow!

741
00:59:02,586 --> 00:59:05,180
Yes, it is an emergency.

742
00:59:05,255 --> 00:59:08,713
No, I can't hold.
Keep me on the line.
Dr. Dickinson.

743
00:59:08,792 --> 00:59:12,023
We've got a healthy kidney
up here. Just Dr. Darrow.

744
00:59:12,095 --> 00:59:14,427
Joe.

745
00:59:14,497 --> 00:59:17,091
Yeah.
Joe, I'm on my way over
to harvest a kidney...

746
00:59:17,167 --> 00:59:20,933
and I want you
to protect it for me.
Tell me what to do.

747
00:59:21,004 --> 00:59:24,599
All right. They're
coming in for other organs,
but that kidney is mine.

748
00:59:24,674 --> 00:59:28,371
I want that made clear
in case anybody choppers in
and tries to grab it.

749
00:59:28,445 --> 00:59:31,710
Stay on top of his vitals.
Don't leave the room
and hold off the vultures.

750
00:59:31,781 --> 00:59:34,409
I don't want anybody cutting
until I get there.
Consider it done.

751
00:59:34,484 --> 00:59:37,715
Put Jeanette
back on the phone, buddy.
I'm ten minutes away.

752
00:59:37,787 --> 00:59:41,120
Jeanette.
Yes, sir.

753
00:59:54,304 --> 00:59:57,273
- You're Dickinson?
- Darrow.

754
00:59:57,340 --> 01:00:01,970
They told me not to leave him,
but I gotta get this monitor
over to the recipient.

755
01:00:02,045 --> 01:00:04,741
I'll keep watch
in here.

756
01:00:04,948 --> 01:00:09,749
Ventilator's set at 16.
That oughta keep
the organs fresh.

757
01:00:41,084 --> 01:00:43,518
[ Helicopter Approaches ]

758
01:01:10,113 --> 01:01:12,013
[ Beeping ]

759
01:01:21,791 --> 01:01:24,385
[ Softly ]
Joe.

760
01:01:32,268 --> 01:01:34,236
Joe.

761
01:01:55,058 --> 01:01:58,926
Come closer.

762
01:02:00,563 --> 01:02:03,225
Dear God.

763
01:02:03,299 --> 01:02:06,029
- [ Man ] We're from Lakeview.
What room's the donor in?
- [ Woman ] 215.

764
01:02:06,102 --> 01:02:10,505
- Double doors on the right.
- Call air support.
I'll be right up.

765
01:02:10,573 --> 01:02:13,007
Guys, we're gonna have to--
[ Continues, lndistinct ]

766
01:02:18,748 --> 01:02:22,275
We're from Lakeview in Lansing.
We have a heart recipient
prepped and ready to go.

767
01:02:22,352 --> 01:02:24,946
You're not supposed to
be in here.
Are you Dickinson?

768
01:02:25,021 --> 01:02:27,148
Get out.
Just get out, please.

769
01:02:27,223 --> 01:02:29,418
- Hey, take it easy, Doctor.
- Get him out of here, all right?

770
01:02:29,492 --> 01:02:31,756
Get everyone out.
Dickinson said--
No, it's okay, Joe.

771
01:02:31,828 --> 01:02:33,887
Dickinson's
in the parking structure.
I just spoke to him.

772
01:02:33,963 --> 01:02:35,897
He said let's move 'em
both into surgery.
Let's go.

773
01:02:35,965 --> 01:02:37,830
Wait, okay?
Hey, Joe.

774
01:02:37,901 --> 01:02:41,997
It's all right.
It's not all right.
He's not ready to be moved.

775
01:02:42,072 --> 01:02:44,802
Hey, what are we waiting for?
Come on. Move him out.

776
01:02:44,874 --> 01:02:47,104
Charlie, wait a second.
What?

777
01:02:47,177 --> 01:02:49,941
This man's not dead.
The brain scan jumped.

778
01:02:50,013 --> 01:02:53,141
I saw it.
I saw it on the monitor.

779
01:02:53,216 --> 01:02:56,310
Come on, Joe.
It's flat as a pancake.
Come on. Move him out of here.

780
01:02:56,386 --> 01:02:58,547
Come on. Let's go.

781
01:02:58,621 --> 01:03:01,419
Charlie, listen.

782
01:03:03,326 --> 01:03:06,227
Charlie, there's
something going on.
Don't do this yet.

783
01:03:06,296 --> 01:03:09,823
Don't kill this man.
Get ahold of yourself.
This man is dead.

784
01:03:09,899 --> 01:03:12,094
He spoke to me.
I'm telling you.
Joe, please.

785
01:03:12,168 --> 01:03:14,728
Joe, this man
did not speak to you.
It was Emily!

786
01:03:14,804 --> 01:03:18,001
It was her voice.
I am not crazy.
You back off.

787
01:03:18,074 --> 01:03:20,008
Don't talk like this.
You've gotta--

788
01:03:20,076 --> 01:03:23,204
You've gotta listen to me.
Charlie, just hold off.

789
01:03:23,279 --> 01:03:26,874
For one minute.
Leave me alone with him.
This is nuts, Joe.

790
01:03:26,950 --> 01:03:30,477
- Come on. Get him inside!
- Hey! Easy! Easy!

791
01:03:30,553 --> 01:03:33,784
Back off, man!
[ Charlie ]
Get him inside!

792
01:03:33,857 --> 01:03:35,882
- Somebody get Security!
- Get him out of here!

793
01:03:35,959 --> 01:03:39,122
- For God's sake, Joe!
- Get Security, will you?

794
01:03:39,195 --> 01:03:42,187
Charlie,
one fucking minute.
Get him outta here!

795
01:03:42,265 --> 01:03:46,463
Joe! We need Security
in two south right away.

796
01:03:46,536 --> 01:03:49,300
Please, listen to me!

797
01:03:49,372 --> 01:03:51,306
[ Groaning ]

798
01:03:52,575 --> 01:03:53,473
[ Sirens Wailing ln Distance ]

799
01:03:57,180 --> 01:03:59,148
[ Chattering ]

800
01:03:59,215 --> 01:04:01,183
All right.

801
01:04:01,251 --> 01:04:03,185
We're going down.
All right.

802
01:04:07,123 --> 01:04:09,489
[ Police Radio Chatter ]
[ Officer Chattering ]

803
01:04:11,828 --> 01:04:13,762
[ Joe ]
Thanks for coming down.

804
01:04:17,467 --> 01:04:21,733
You posted bail?
First offense.
Got it waived.

805
01:04:21,804 --> 01:04:25,331
I also spoke to the hospital
administrator who's willing
to drop all charges...

806
01:04:25,408 --> 01:04:29,242
if you'll agree to take
a lengthy sabbatical.
I'll bet.

807
01:04:29,312 --> 01:04:33,840
He said you claimed
a brain-dead organ donor
spoke to you. Is that true?

808
01:04:33,917 --> 01:04:36,715
No.
Good.

809
01:04:38,354 --> 01:04:40,845
It was Emily.

810
01:04:42,091 --> 01:04:45,549
Speaking through him.
[ Sighs ]

811
01:04:45,628 --> 01:04:49,359
You know, I could almost
understand it with the kids,
because they all knew her.

812
01:04:49,432 --> 01:04:52,265
Of course
they're gonna dream about her.
She was key to their survival.

813
01:04:52,335 --> 01:04:55,065
Okay, then how about
the kid who never even
laid eyes on her?

814
01:04:55,138 --> 01:04:58,972
What kid?
The kid I told you about
in the kitchen.

815
01:04:59,042 --> 01:05:01,806
The first time he ever met her
was in a coma, Miriam.
Remember?

816
01:05:01,878 --> 01:05:04,711
I've got his admission records
to prove it.

817
01:05:04,781 --> 01:05:08,308
That's evidence, right?
lsn't that what you wanted?

818
01:05:08,384 --> 01:05:12,047
She's trying to reach me,
and she's becoming desperate.

819
01:05:12,121 --> 01:05:15,579
Why?
Why desperate, Joe?

820
01:05:19,495 --> 01:05:21,827
Oh, you don't think
she's still alive.

821
01:05:21,898 --> 01:05:24,731
If a kid could see her
in a coma, then why...

822
01:05:24,801 --> 01:05:27,269
couldn't she be trying to
communicate from one?

823
01:05:27,337 --> 01:05:32,240
There were no survivors.
The Venezuelan government
searched the jungle for a month.

824
01:05:32,308 --> 01:05:35,334
And never found her!
Exactly. And that's
why we're here tonight--

825
01:05:35,411 --> 01:05:38,744
because you never saw her body
and never got closure.

826
01:05:42,518 --> 01:05:44,452
Emily's dead, Joe.

827
01:05:45,688 --> 01:05:47,622
That's what
this is all about--

828
01:05:47,690 --> 01:05:49,681
your refusal
to accept that.

829
01:05:50,960 --> 01:05:53,428
Look.
I understand it.

830
01:05:53,496 --> 01:05:56,590
If I hadn't seen Hannah's body,
I wouldn't have believed it
either.

831
01:05:56,666 --> 01:05:59,760
I'd still be waiting
for her to come home,
just like you are.

832
01:06:01,371 --> 01:06:04,363
You have to
end this, Joe.

833
01:06:04,440 --> 01:06:07,898
You gotta
do the hard stuff,
like I did.

834
01:06:07,977 --> 01:06:10,036
Like everyone does.

835
01:06:10,113 --> 01:06:13,276
You gotta
clean out the closets,
empty the drawers...

836
01:06:13,349 --> 01:06:18,048
and take down the vacancy sign
that says "Emily's ghost
is welcome here"...

837
01:06:18,121 --> 01:06:20,988
and get on with your life
without her.

838
01:06:26,796 --> 01:06:28,787
[ Bag Crinkling ]

839
01:06:30,466 --> 01:06:32,400
[ Softly ]
All right.

840
01:06:36,906 --> 01:06:38,840
What about
that rafting trip?

841
01:06:40,476 --> 01:06:42,410
What do you mean,
what about it?

842
01:06:42,478 --> 01:06:45,447
Well, anything to get
your mind off of this.

843
01:06:45,515 --> 01:06:47,449
So, you think
I should go?

844
01:06:47,517 --> 01:06:49,951
Maybe I'll go
with you. Huh?

845
01:06:50,019 --> 01:06:52,715
I'm mean with a paddle.
[ Chuckles ]

846
01:06:54,090 --> 01:06:56,183
The river's up
this time of year.

847
01:06:56,259 --> 01:06:59,422
It's gone from
a two-point difficulty
to a five.

848
01:06:59,495 --> 01:07:02,328
I want us all to go home,
go over our river maps.

849
01:07:02,398 --> 01:07:05,424
Note the hazard points,
the portages, the waterfalls.

850
01:07:05,501 --> 01:07:08,163
Oh, check out
these safari pants.
It says to pack light.

851
01:07:08,237 --> 01:07:10,899
I'm just bringing my thong.
Well, then,
I'm bringing my camera.

852
01:07:10,973 --> 01:07:14,500
Well, it better be disposable,
because it's likely everything
is going into the drink.

853
01:07:14,577 --> 01:07:17,444
Speaking of drink,
here's to adventure.

854
01:07:17,513 --> 01:07:19,447
Yeah!
Adventure.

855
01:07:27,156 --> 01:07:29,090
[ Dog Barking ln Distance ]

856
01:07:36,833 --> 01:07:38,767
What do you think?

857
01:07:39,902 --> 01:07:42,234
I think it's an idea
whose time has come.

858
01:07:42,305 --> 01:07:46,537
[ Chuckles ]
No, I mean-- I mean,
do you think it'll sell?

859
01:07:46,609 --> 01:07:48,600
The agent said
it needed a paint job.

860
01:07:48,644 --> 01:07:51,306
Oh, get what you can
and get out.

861
01:07:51,381 --> 01:07:54,942
Leave the memories behind.
You didn't after Hannah died.

862
01:07:55,017 --> 01:07:58,646
Yeah, but I didn't have corpses
playing ventriloquist
with me either.

863
01:07:58,721 --> 01:08:00,882
[ Both Laughing ]

864
01:08:00,957 --> 01:08:04,290
I'm gonna miss you, Joe.

865
01:08:04,360 --> 01:08:06,294
I'm gonna
miss your waffles.

866
01:08:09,766 --> 01:08:13,293
Would you show it for me
if I'm gone for a week?

867
01:08:13,369 --> 01:08:17,430
- I'm taking that white-water trip.
- With pleasure.

868
01:08:17,507 --> 01:08:19,941
It's good to see you
joining the world again.

869
01:08:23,179 --> 01:08:25,841
[ Car Door Opens,
Closes ]

870
01:09:45,962 --> 01:09:47,930
[ Lightbulb Crackling ]

871
01:09:49,232 --> 01:09:51,894
[ Lightbulb Pops ]

872
01:10:12,588 --> 01:10:15,523
[ Clattering, Footsteps ]

873
01:11:09,011 --> 01:11:10,945
[ Front Door Creaking ]

874
01:11:16,052 --> 01:11:17,986
[ Creaking ]

875
01:11:30,099 --> 01:11:32,033
[ Wind Chimes Jingling ]

876
01:12:56,218 --> 01:12:58,948
[ Hal ] Hello.
Hal. Reading the map
of the river...

877
01:12:59,021 --> 01:13:02,752
there's a symbol--
two wavery lines that
crisscross in the middle.

878
01:13:02,825 --> 01:13:06,989
Waterfalls. Put a big
red circle around those.
We'll have to portage there.

879
01:13:07,063 --> 01:13:08,997
They're too high
this time of year.

880
01:13:11,367 --> 01:13:13,301
Joe?

881
01:13:45,000 --> 01:13:47,628
A rainbow.

882
01:14:10,126 --> 01:14:12,185
You are, uh,
the doctor?
Yes.

883
01:14:12,261 --> 01:14:14,320
Muy bien.

884
01:14:14,396 --> 01:14:16,330
[ Speaking Spanish ]

885
01:14:18,701 --> 01:14:22,296
Is my pilot here?
That is me.
Eh, Victor.

886
01:14:23,506 --> 01:14:25,701
¿Cómo te vas?

887
01:14:25,775 --> 01:14:29,677
I take you bags.
You been flying long,
Victor?

888
01:14:29,745 --> 01:14:32,339
Don't worry.
I know how.

889
01:14:32,414 --> 01:14:35,110
You have a license,
though, right?
;Sí.

890
01:14:35,184 --> 01:14:37,152
Pretty much.

891
01:14:42,625 --> 01:14:44,616
Juanajuapa.

892
01:14:44,693 --> 01:14:46,627
Juanajuapa,
you've been there?

893
01:14:46,695 --> 01:14:48,560
Sí, Juanajuapa.

894
01:14:49,698 --> 01:14:52,565
This is it, right?

895
01:14:53,636 --> 01:14:55,661
With the waterfall?

896
01:14:55,738 --> 01:14:59,538
I don't know.
I've only been there
in the dry season.

897
01:15:03,279 --> 01:15:07,181
Is my interpreter here?
The Yanomami
speak a little Spanish.

898
01:15:07,249 --> 01:15:09,581
I speak a little Guaharibo.

899
01:15:09,652 --> 01:15:11,984
You talk to them
through me.

900
01:15:12,054 --> 01:15:14,488
Okay, we go.

901
01:15:25,267 --> 01:15:29,636
Is that your girlfriend?
ln the picture?

902
01:15:29,705 --> 01:15:32,196
It's my wife.

903
01:15:32,274 --> 01:15:34,265
Used to be.

904
01:15:35,778 --> 01:15:39,009
You come
to get her back, eh?

905
01:15:41,083 --> 01:15:43,017
In a way, I guess.

906
01:15:55,598 --> 01:15:57,964
There was an accident
here last spring.

907
01:15:58,033 --> 01:16:01,525
A bus?
That washed away
on a road?

908
01:16:01,604 --> 01:16:04,630
La Cruz Roja.
The Red Cross.
Yes, that's right.

909
01:16:04,707 --> 01:16:08,108
You can probably see it
now that the river's
not so high.

910
01:16:08,177 --> 01:16:10,645
It's just up ahead.
It's on the way.

911
01:16:14,183 --> 01:16:16,947
The rock slide took more
than just a bus.

912
01:16:17,019 --> 01:16:20,580
It isolated an entire tribe
from the outside world.

913
01:16:20,656 --> 01:16:23,557
Can you see it
down there?

914
01:16:28,163 --> 01:16:30,222
Nobody lived.

915
01:16:30,299 --> 01:16:33,097
The Yanomami are still wearing
some of their clothing.

916
01:16:34,169 --> 01:16:37,332
That's Juanajuapa
up ahead.

917
01:16:37,406 --> 01:16:40,466
Some of the bodies
washed out of the bus...

918
01:16:40,542 --> 01:16:43,067
down the river
and right into the village.

919
01:17:06,001 --> 01:17:07,935
[ Victor ]
The guides we are meeting...

920
01:17:08,003 --> 01:17:10,369
they work with
all the tribes
in the area.

921
01:17:11,640 --> 01:17:14,438
Did I mention
they don't like outsiders?

922
01:17:21,383 --> 01:17:23,749
It's a good thing
you have me with you.

923
01:17:31,961 --> 01:17:34,395
[ Speaking Native Language ]

924
01:17:37,366 --> 01:17:39,300
[ Speaking Native Language ]

925
01:18:05,527 --> 01:18:09,258
He said he cannot take you
to the village.

926
01:18:09,331 --> 01:18:14,268
But, for a price,
he can take you
to their graves.

927
01:20:01,410 --> 01:20:03,378
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

928
01:20:34,176 --> 01:20:36,110
Señor.

929
01:20:37,179 --> 01:20:39,647
Señor.

930
01:20:39,715 --> 01:20:41,649
We should go.

931
01:20:47,289 --> 01:20:50,452
They, uh...

932
01:20:50,526 --> 01:20:54,292
they wouldn't know,
would they, which, uh...

933
01:20:54,363 --> 01:20:56,297
body was buried where?

934
01:20:58,901 --> 01:21:01,597
Look. If--
If the weather gets...

935
01:21:01,670 --> 01:21:04,605
any worse,
we don't get outta here.

936
01:21:04,673 --> 01:21:06,607
And-- And that's
no good for nobody.

937
01:21:12,381 --> 01:21:14,315
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

938
01:21:22,591 --> 01:21:25,526
[ Speaking Native Language ]

939
01:21:33,435 --> 01:21:35,995
Señors.

940
01:21:36,071 --> 01:21:38,005
Señors, uh...

941
01:21:38,073 --> 01:21:40,837
my wife.
Su esposa.

942
01:21:40,909 --> 01:21:43,776
Mi esposa.
Red Cross.

943
01:21:43,845 --> 01:21:47,144
- La Cruz Roja.
- Cruz Roja. Where?

944
01:21:47,216 --> 01:21:49,184
¿Dónde?
¿Dónde?

945
01:21:49,251 --> 01:21:51,913
Does any--
Does anybody know where?

946
01:21:51,987 --> 01:21:54,956
[ Speaking Native Language ]
Which one?

947
01:21:55,023 --> 01:21:58,151
[ Speaking Native Language ]

948
01:22:00,495 --> 01:22:03,828
- What are they saying?
- They say they know her.

949
01:22:03,899 --> 01:22:06,891
[ Speaking Native Language ]

950
01:22:13,008 --> 01:22:17,206
What's he saying now?
He says he wants to
take you to the village.

951
01:22:17,279 --> 01:22:19,975
And he says that, no,
you need permission.

952
01:22:20,048 --> 01:22:23,142
- [ Speaking Native Language ]
- What is he saying?
What the hell is he saying?

953
01:22:23,218 --> 01:22:24,742
- I-l don't know!
- [ Speaking Native Language ]

954
01:22:45,007 --> 01:22:46,941
Señor!

955
01:22:48,610 --> 01:22:52,341
Señor, you cannot
go into the village!
It is forbidden, señor!

956
01:22:55,851 --> 01:22:59,343
Señor! Señor, stop!

